                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d494">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.24/38: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-28T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 28, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>279. Please inform the Department whether the Liberian Government is now prepared
                    to proceed in the matter of Lend-Lease aid. If so, authorization should be
                    telegraphed to Consul General Walker to sign the standard form of
                    representations mentioned in the Department’s 51, March 12, 8 p.m., in order
                    that an appropriate announcement may be made at the same time that a statement
                    is issued regarding the presence of American forces in Liberia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
